<a href="javascript:card_browser(33)">Saruman&#39;s Power</a>    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> This is the deck you probably always see in every tournament, with just a few little modifications.  Has yet to lose in the one local tournament i played in, and hasnt lost to my friends yet with all kinds of deck strategies (20 games or so).<br>
<br>
To start bid 2.  This is only going to hurt if your playing nazgul.  But that&#39;s why you can remove burdens with Narya and prevent burdens with Melilot, who can heal every turn with your rare Frodo.  If you win go ahead and go first, and get gandalf&#39;s cart to hold toys before the people actually show up.  It never takes long to find companions.  When you do, just give them their things from the cart.  Gandalf get&#39;s strongest when you have several companions out.  he&#39;s probably a base strength 10 by then.  And you should probably spot 3 gandalf sig&#39;s for the trust me&#39;s.  He&#39;s got plenty of vitality so don&#39;t be afraid to use the card if it&#39;s going to help you win skirmishes.  The companions that are there don&#39;t really need much explanation.  Hopefully, aragorn and gimli will stay around for a long time as they have the gandalf signets and have enough good equipment to live to site 9.  Arwen always seems to die some way or another, even though her stuff is there.  She is another gandalf sig to spot, and is good with ditching cards via gwemegil and is thoretically hard to take down.  Sam is there to take on the cave troll and the balrog at the same time, or just if you think it&#39;s funny to see him explode.  I do.  Boromir can&#39;t be overwhelmed, almost.  So if all else is failing and they toss a balrog at you, he can step in front of the Rog a couple times instead of having Gandalf or someone else having to face him.  He&#39;s there to die, so take advantage of that.  Greenleaf just shoots a couple minions like Goblin Scavs, and until then adds to the archery total.  Then after he&#39;s used his ability to the max you can make him face lurtz or something else.  Thrarin&#39;s job is to die before he gets discarded at site 7, if it&#39;s going to apply.  If all is going well, and it usually is, just run to site 9.<br>
<br>
The shadow is just to throw what you can at them.  Discard minions if you have too many in your hand at once, and focus pumps into overwhelming people if you can.  The palantir can be fun.  If they rely on conditions too heavily, then you have a saruman&#39;s power to screw them over.  They arent going to be very keen on moving again on a couple uruk-hai so this helps your fellowship stay ahead if that&#39;s what you decide to do. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=25952"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=25952" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
